Business Rules (ServiceNow)
🔹 What are Business Rules?

Business Rules are server-side scripts in ServiceNow that execute when a record is displayed, inserted, updated, deleted, or queried. They automate processes and enforce business logic.

🔹 Features
Runs on the server side
Automates record processing
Validates and updates data
Executes based on conditions
Reduces manual work
🔹 Types of Business Rules
1. Before

Runs before the record is saved to the database.

Use Cases:

Validate data
Modify field values before saving

Example:
Automatically set Priority before record insertion.

2. After

Runs after the record is saved.

Use Cases:

Trigger notifications
Create related records

Example:
Send notification after incident creation.

3. Async (Asynchronous)

Runs in the background after database operations.

Use Cases:

Email notifications
Background processing
External integrations

Example:
Generate reports after update.

4. Display

Runs when the form loads and sends data to the client.

Use Cases:

Populate client-side values
Pass data using g_scratchpad

Example:
Display additional information on form load.

🔹 Components
Name → Business Rule name
Table → Target table
When → Before / After / Async / Display
Condition → Defines execution criteria
Script → Contains business logic
🔹 Example

Scenario:
If Priority is High, set Impact = High

if(current.priority == 1){
current.impact = 1;
}
🔹 Benefits
Automates business processes
Maintains data integrity
Reduces repetitive tasks
Improves efficiency
🔹 Business Rules vs Client Scripts
Business Rules	Client Scripts
Server-side	Client-side
Runs on database actions	Runs in browser
Uses current object	Uses g_form
Handles backend logic	Handles UI interactions
